{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17648504","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17648504"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:54:32+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:54:32+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18317"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18317","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18317"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.1,0.1,0.38,0.33,0.1]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11035"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"77484"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11035","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11035"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18317"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62996"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4944"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25606"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25611"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26548"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"77484","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/77484"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe risk of post-operative infection will vary with the site and type of procedure and the general state of health of the patient.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following medical procedures is most commonly associated with the development of chronic osteomyelitis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Arthroscopy","Partial joint replacement","Total joint replacement","Osteotomy","Meniscus repair"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EChronic osteomyelitis is a persistent bone infection that can occur after certain medical procedures. It is characterised by inflammation and bone destruction, often requiring long-term treatment.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETotal joint replacement\u003C/strong\u003E is the medical procedure most commonly associated with the development of chronic osteomyelitis. This is due to the potential for bacterial contamination during the surgery, which can lead to a persistent infection in the bone.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EArthroscopy\u003C/strong\u003E - This is a less invasive procedure with a lower risk of infection compared to joint replacement\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPartial joint replacement\u003C/strong\u003E - While it can lead to infection, the risk is generally lower than with total joint replacement\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOsteotomy\u003C/strong\u003E - This procedure involves cutting and reshaping bone, but is less commonly associated with chronic osteomyelitis\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMeniscus repair\u003C/strong\u003E - This is a soft tissue procedure with a lower risk of bone infection\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Chronic osteomyelitis is often associated with surgical procedures involving bone, such as total joint replacement.","Infections can occur after surgical procedures due to the introduction of bacteria during the operation.","Total joint replacement is a common procedure that can lead to chronic osteomyelitis if infection occurs."],"references":["Sud, A., \u0026 Ranjan, R. (2021). Textbook of Orthopaedics, 2e-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Mohan, H. (2018). Textbook of pathology. Jaypee Brothers Medical Publishers","Momodu II, Savaliya V. Osteomyelitis. [Updated 2023 May 31]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK532250/","Folpe, A., \u0026 Nielsen, G. P. (Eds.). (2022). Bone and Soft Tissue Pathology E-Book: A Volume in the Foundations in Diagnostic Pathology Series. Elsevier Health Sciences","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62996"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18317"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62996","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/62996"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-07T09:15:02+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-07T09:15:25+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11035"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"77484"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"des